<TITLE> 'Extremist' killed in Faridpur shootout </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Oct 6 (bdnews24.com)A suspected extremist was killed and another injured in separate encounters with RAB and police in Faridpur and Jhenaidah early on Tuesday and Monday night. The dead man, 34 year old Lavlu Byapari was a member of extremist outfit Purbo Banglar Communist Party (Janajuddha-ML), RAB said in a statement. RAB-8 Faridpur camp commander Flt Lt Moinul Alam told bdnews24.com that patrol teams of the elite force and police cordoned off the Jashim Mancha at Ambikapur at around 4am on a tip-off that a group of extremists were gathering there. The criminals fired and the law-enforcers retaliated, he said. Lavlu died at one stage of the shootout, Alam also said and added that three firearms and seven cartridges were recovered from the scene. Kotwali police chief Noor-e-Alam Siddiqui said Lavlu faced 17 cases. He was a fugitive lifetime convict in a case filed under the explosives act. In Jhenaidah, Jenarul Islam was injured on Monday night at Harinakundu upazila during an armed encounter with RAB and police. RAB said Jenarul was also an operative of Purba Banglar Communist Party. Jhenaidah RAB's Major Sayef Ali told bdnews24.com they had arrested Jenarul in front of Harinakundu Upazila Prishad. Following his confessional statement the elite force and police launched a drive at Gobrapara village to recover arms where Jenarul's associates who had taken position there earlier opened fire on the law-enforcers who fired back. At one stage, Jenaul received bullet wounds as he was trying to flee the scene. Two members of RAB and police were also injured at the time, Sayef said. Jenarul was admitted to Jhenaidah General Hospital. He faced one murder and one bomb explosion cases, the RAB official said. One shutter gun and three rounds of bullets were recovered from the scene. bdne
